-- U.S. judge tosses Miami mortgage discrimination suit against BofA
-- By Dena Aubin
-- Wed Jul 09, 2014 10:48AM EDT
-- None



July 9 (Reuters) - A federal judge has dismissed a lawsuit brought by the City of Miami against Bank of America Corp <BAC.N> for mortgage discrimination, ruling the city lacked legal standing to sue for damages under the U.S. Fair Housing Act.

